cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving the performance of Neural Machine Translation (NMT) models during the decoding phase. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes two dynamic oracle-based methods to improve the performance of NMT models, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also discusses changing the training process towards a less guided scheme, which involves optimizing the model's parameters, making cs.LG (Learning) another possible category. Additionally, the paper uses experimental results to evaluate the proposed approaches, which involves statistical analysis and data visualization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with improving the translation quality of NMT models, which involves image and video processing techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another possible category.
